{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "We annotated the hitting sounds produced during strokes as \"good\", \"maybe\", or \"bad\" to provide insight into the quality of the stroke and the skill of the player.",
    "As mentioned in the interview responses of badminton coaches in the Dataset Design section, making a good shot depends on the strike impact of the racket on the shuttlecock, and the sound generated during a stroke is an important factor in evaluating a player's skill.",
    "The sound of the stroke was collected using the sensor mounted on the Pupil Invisible glasses and annotated using the recorded eye video.",
    "To ensure the validity of annotations, three HCI researchers performed the annotations, and inter-rater reliability was later calculated to measure the consistency of the annotation values between the researchers.",
    "We classified the sound as \"good\" when it resembled the sound made when a professional player hits the shuttlecock squarely."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}